BRUCELLOSIS, HUMAN, BOVINE - VENEZUELA
**************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Sponsored in part by Elsevier, publisher of Tuberculosis
<http://thelancet.url123.com/a5dpp>
Date: 27 Sep 2005 [the delay in posting is regretted. - ProMED]
From: Alfonso J. Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Weekly Epidemiological Bulletin (Boletin Epidemiologico Semanal)
11-19 Sep 2005 [in Spanish, trans. Mod.JGM; edited]
<http://www.msds.gov.ve/msds/Boletines/Alertas/2005>

Zoonoses Regional Coordination from the State of Aragua notified for the
current epidemiological week [11-19 Sep 2005]: 1 confirmed case of human
brucellosis, from the community of Giradot.
Regional Coordination from the State of Bolivar notified 22 confirmed cases of
brucellosis in cattle from the community of Caroni.
Zoonoses Regional Coordination from the State of Apure notified 40 probable
cases of human brucellosis from the following communities: San Fernando (31),
Biruaca (5), and Guarico (4).
Zoonoses Regional Coordination from the State of Lara notified 14 probable
human brucellosis cases, from the community of Pala Vecino, Jose G. Bastidas
parish.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This report does not give the time frame of dates of onset of the cases.
Geographically Apure and Lara states are in the Western part of the country
with Lara to the north and Apure bordering with Colombia
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/venezuela.gif>. - Mod.MPP]
[Elsevier reference: Dokuzouza B. et al. 2005. Characteristics of B.
melitensis versus B. abortus bacteraemias. Journal of Infection Volume 50,
Issue 1 , Pages 41-45]
[CDC reference: Brucellosis <http://www.bt.cdc.gov/agent/brucellosis>]
